  <chapter id="intro">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
      This document describes how normal users can interact via the dancer IRC server. It is
      intended as a guide and reference for users and channel operators, specifically on the
      <ulink url="http://www.freenode.net/">Freenode</ulink> network (FN).
    </para>
    <para>
      This is not a beginners guide to IRC. For help with general IRC commands, visit 
      <ulink url="http://www.irchelp.org/">www.irchelp.org</ulink>. This document only
      extends to the things which are different in dancer, and channel management on FN.
    </para>
    <para>
      FN exists primarily to provide IRC hosting for opensource projects and things associated with
      them, along with all kinds of other community-oriented groups. Note that it is not primarily a
      chat network, and it is most definately not for pr0n/music/warez trading or cracker
      activities. It's IRC server has been designed to promote calm, reasoned discourse, in
      accordance with <ulink url="http://www.freenode.net/philosophy.shtml">FN philosophy</ulink>.
    </para>
  </chapter>
